        <h2 class="text-info" id="general-questions-functionality"><b>General Questions - Functionality</b></h2>

        <h3 class="my-3" id="general-questions-upload-a-note"><b>1. How to upload a note?</b></h3>
        <p>To upload a note, log in to your account, navigate to the "Upload Note" section, select the appropriate category and sub-category, attach your PDF file, add relevant tags, and click "Submit".</p>

        <h3 class="my-3" id="general-questions-create-category"><b>2. How to create a category?</b></h3>
        <p>Only administrators can create categories. If you need a new category, please contact the support team or submit a request through the "Submit Ticket" section.</p>

        <h3 class="my-3" id="general-questions-apply-tags"><b>3. How to apply tags?</b></h3>
        <p>When uploading a note, you can add tags in the designated field. Simply type the relevant keywords and press enter to add each tag. Tags help in categorizing and searching for notes more efficiently.</p>

        <h3 class="my-3" id="general-questions-leave-review"><b>4. How to leave a review?</b></h3>
        <p>To leave a review, go to the note you wish to review, scroll down to the review section, select a rating between 1 and 5 stars, and leave your comments. Click "Submit" to post your review.</p>

        <h3 class="my-3" id="general-questions-search-notes"><b>5. How to search for notes?</b></h3>
        <p>Use the search bar at the top of the page to enter keywords, tags, or categories. You can also apply filters based on ratings and categories to narrow down the results.</p>

        <h3 class="my-3" id="general-questions-download-notes"><b>6. How to download notes?</b></h3>
        <p>To download a note, navigate to the note you wish to download and click on the "Download" button. The file will be saved to your device.</p>

        <h3 class="my-3" id="general-questions-google-drive"><b>7. How to upload notes to Google Drive?</b></h3>
        <p>When uploading a note, you have the option to save a copy to your Google Drive. Check the "Save to Google Drive" option during the upload process and authenticate your Google account if prompted.</p>

